\ls2\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\fs26 An index is the place where the data used by a search engine is stored. It is the equivalent for search of what a \'93table\'94 is for a database. Unlike a database table, an index is optimized for search operations.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs24 {\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}
\fs26 A record is our way to describe a single object. For example, if you have a database of clothes that you sell on your website, one single unique piece of clothing is referred to as a record. We also refer the search results as records.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	\
The metrics that would be useful depends on your business. Let\'92s say a user searches for \'93Popular Restaurants\'94 you might want to rank it based on its number of reviews and ratings to provide relevant results.\
You can refer to this link for more information about Custom Ranking: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/managing-results/must-do/custom-ranking/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/managing-results/must-do/custom-ranking/}}\
\
I am here to assist and make your onboarding process smoother. Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have further questions. You can email me or give me a call directly at 123-456-7890. \
\
Thank you again for your interest in Algolia.\
\
