\
Hi Matt,\
\
Thank you for reaching out to Algolia! I am sorry that the new dashboard design does not meet your expectations and I understand that having extra steps can lead to inconvenience. We are always trying to improve our product and I have forwarded your feedback to our design/engineering team. \
\
The new dashboard design is integrated to support our new XYZ feature and speeds up ABC, so that users can create and update indices instantly. We also included an easier way to upload your data and configure all of your settings within one page. We are sorry that it takes several clicks to delete/clear indexes. Please be assured that our development work is prioritized for our clients\'92 needs and to provide the best user experience.\
\
Here are several ways I find very simple to delete/clear indexes:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	0.	}To clear a single index:\uc0\u8232 click Indices -> Manage Index -> Delete\
{\listtext	0.	}To clear multiple indices: \uc0\u8232 click Indices -> click the top left Indices -> Select all indices you want to delete -> Delete Indices\u8232 Note: you can also delete a single index using this method\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
I hope you found a preferable option for these tasks. Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have further concerns or feedback regarding our product.\
